  "diary": "Started the day right—watering the basil and tomatoes on the roof while the sun was still soft. The city was quiet, almost mine alone. The shift at Interbay was the usual chaos: a MVA around noon, a diabetic crisis, the constant hum of monitors and urgent calls. By 4pm I was ready to be anywhere else. Light Rail home felt like a decompression chamber. I caught the garden again in that golden afternoon light, then walked over to Serious Pie to avoid the Pride crowds gathering downtown. Capitol Hill was already buzzing—I could hear the energy even from a distance, all that joy and color. Back home, I put on some Coltrane, let the whole evening unfold slowly. Made pasta with my own basil, read a bit, tended the garden one last time as the sky turned purple. Felt good to be here, quiet and contained, while the city celebrated outside.",
